DEEP DIVE: BELIEF SYSTEMS & LETTING GO

The Question from the Participant

A participant named Ciao asked about belief systems, noting:
• Bashar has said in the past that once you realize a negative belief system doesn't make sense, you let it go
• The participant has seen this happen and knows it to be true
• However, they've been surprised by negative encounters or feelings
• When asking "What do I have to believe about myself to feel this way?" the answers revealed beliefs they didn't realize they had
• Examples included: "not being good enough"
• They tried to reason it out: "Creation doesn't make mistakes, so I exist, I'm worthy, I'm valid, I love myself"
• But the issues persist
• Consciously they don't feel like they have that belief system
• They're aware of a possible lack of awareness

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

BASHAR'S RESPONSE: STRENGTHENING THE LETTING GO

The Core Issue: Did You Really Let Go?

• Perhaps you have to strengthen the part of the exercise that has to do with: Did you in fact actually let go?
• Did you really understand that it's not true?
• Did you really let go of that idea that you're not worthy (as an example)?

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

THE FEAR BENEATH THE BELIEF

The Critical Question

• Are you afraid that something else will happen if you let that go?
• If you really are willing to be your true self in your society
• Are you afraid of something else happening when you are your true self?

The Exploration Needed

• Explore that side of the equation
• What are you afraid might happen if you did let go of those particular definitions that you're discovering popping up in your unconscious mind?
• What would really happen?
• What do you believe might happen that you wouldn't prefer?
• What might you be afraid of?

The Invitation

• Bashar encourages exploring this at greater depth
• The persistence of negative beliefs often indicates a fear of what might happen if you truly let them go
• There is often a hidden belief that the limiting belief is somehow protecting you from something worse

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

UNDERSTANDING THE LAYERS OF BELIEF

The Surface vs. The Depth

• Consciously, you may believe you've let go of a limiting belief
• You may understand logically why the belief isn't true
• You may have reasoned through why you are worthy, valid, and loved
• Yet the belief persists

The Hidden Protection Mechanism

• The persistence indicates there's a deeper layer
• Often, the subconscious believes that holding onto the limiting belief protects you from something
• Questions to explore:
  - What am I afraid will happen if I am fully my true self?
  - What consequences am I avoiding by holding onto unworthiness?
  - What safety does this limiting belief provide?
  - What might I have to face or do if I truly believed I was worthy?
  - What might change in my relationships if I let this go?
  - What might change in my life circumstances if I let this go?

The Real Work

• The real work is not just recognizing the limiting belief
• The real work is discovering what you believe that limiting belief is protecting you from
• Once you discover the fear beneath the belief, you can address that fear directly
• Then the limiting belief can truly be released because it no longer serves a protective function

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

KEY PRINCIPLES SUMMARY

The Foundation of Physical Reality
• Physical reality is a projection of consciousness within your awareness
• It is a densification/crystallization of spiritual energy
• You chose this experience for your own growth and purposes
• Physical reality offers unique experiences that cannot be had in spirit

The Benefits of Physical Experience
• Builds a repertoire and library of experiences
• Allows you to become a living example for others
• Develops mastery of limitations
• Creates new perspectives and relationships with space-time
• Serves as a musical instrument to create beautiful orchestrations

The Path of Mastery
• Stay within positive frameworks and belief systems
• Apply creativity and imagination to every experience
• Always ask: "How can this serve me?"
• Take responsibility for choosing this physical experience
• Become a teacher and living example for others

The Practice of Presence
• Physical reality only exists in the present moment
• Do not worry about past or future
• Be present as fully, boldly, and lovingly as you can
• Act from that presence

The Truth About Beliefs
• Examine your beliefs and choose ones that work for you
• If a limiting belief persists despite conscious understanding, explore what you're afraid might happen if you let it go
• Often beliefs persist because they serve a hidden protective function
• The real work is discovering and addressing the fear beneath the belief
• Physical reality becomes more flexible, magical, and synchronistic as you expand your awareness
• You are a master class soul, not a backward being
• Physical reality is a gift and an art form to be mastered

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

PRACTICAL APPLICATION

Questions to Ask Yourself

When encountering persistent limiting beliefs:

1. "Have I truly let this belief go, or am I still holding onto it?"

2. "What am I afraid might happen if I completely let go of this belief?"

3. "If I were fully my true self without this limiting belief, what would change in my life?"

4. "What does this limiting belief protect me from?"

5. "What consequences am I avoiding by holding onto this belief?"

6. "Am I afraid of something else happening if I am my true self in my society?"

7. "What would really happen if I let this go completely?"

The Transformation Process

• Recognize the limiting belief consciously
• Understand logically why it isn't true
• Go deeper: Explore what fear is beneath the belief
• Address that underlying fear directly
• Then the limiting belief can truly be released
• Take responsibility for choosing physical reality
• Use every experience to serve yourself and others
• Be present and act from presence
• Allow physical reality to become your musical instrument
• Play it uniquely, harmoniously, beautifully

